ipSecTunnelStatus.name: ipSecTunnelStatus
ipSecTunnelStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to: 1) allow user-data traffic flow through this tunnel by setting this the value of this object to active (1). 2 bring the tunnel down by setting the value of this object to destroy(2). 3) stop all user-data traffic flow through the tunnel by setting the value of this object to disable(3). This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row. Valid Status Changes New Status +---------+---------+---------+ Current Status | active | destroy | disable | +---------------+=========+=========+=========+ | active | Valid | Valid | Valid | +---------------+---------+---------+---------+ | destroy | Invalid | Invalid | Invalid | +---------------+---------+---------+---------+ | disable | Valid | Valid | Valid | +---------------+---------+---------+---------+
